Text.Value: Talk to Sticky. Until I come to collect, our business is done.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, angry - we told her that we killed her patron and she plans to get us back some day

Text.Value: So what if it is? Choosing the right allies is just common sense. You wouldn't have made it this far on your own.
This is just a hiccup though. I'll still run this city one day, with or without Raph. And when I do, my Guild won't look on you too kindly.
I wouldn't miss it for the world. Baldur's Gate is home now, and the Brats are my family. Nobody messes with my family.
I hope you don't regret this, Mol.
Come find me when I'm running this whole Guild, and see how easily the gold wipes away any regrets I do have.
You always were sharp, if a bit slow. Too big to be quick. But I'll stay out of your way if you'll stay out of mine.
Give me that. Can't have this floating around loose. I thought I was meant to be the thief?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Standard 'receive item out of shot' animation

Text.Value: I knew you'd understand. Everyone's owned by somebody - might as well sign up to be on the winning team.
Once they realise that, they'll be looking for a... mediator. Someone to speak for the crews. I'll be right here.
Big Raph doesn't own me - he's just giving me the tools to keep myself alive, and to take what I want.
How did you escape Moonrise?
So what if it is? Choosing the right allies is just common sense. Even you'll make a friend or two eventually, I bet.
Leave.
Why? Don't know about you, but I don't put my name to something I don't mean.
Well, look who it is. Glad to see you in the city - hope you found plenty of coin in Ketheric's coffers.

EditorData.NodeContext: A fond greeting - ribbing is as close to affection as she'll get

Text.Value: There'll be no Guild to run if the city falls. Can I count on your help when the fighting begins?
What else? The Guildhall is still standing, even if Nine-Fingers isn't. Just means there's a chair to be filled.
Now if you're here for business, talk to Sticky. I don't deal directly with the customers.
I'll leave the frontline hero work to the likes of you. We'll be here to pick up the pieces when you're done.
A pact is just another deal. He can call himself 'patron', but Big Raph doesn't own me - he's just giving me the tools to take what I want.
You're still trading? Aren't you concerned with the new management?
Why would you sign a deal with a devil?
Raphael's dead, Mol. I killed him.
I survived the hells when Elturel fell. Compared to that, slipping out of Moonrise was child's play.
Sure is. We work for Fetcher, handling what you might call pre-owned goods. Talk to Sticky, he'll cut you a deal.
Good to see you again. What are you up to this time?
This will end badly, Mol. Everyone who takes a devil's deal thinks they'll be in control.
Make sure we're all on the winning team. There's a fight for the city's survival coming, and I'll need your help.
Leave.
Show me what you're capable of. There's a fight for the city's survival coming - can I count on your help?
Is this a Guild business you're running here?
I'm impressed. You saw an opportunity for power and you took it.
Is this how you survived the shadowlands? A deal with Raphael?
As for what that is, well... you didn't think I planned to stop at running the Fetcher's Brats, did you?
You... bloody idiot. You can kill half the devils in the hells for all I care - but Raphael was my patron. He made promises.
Oh, I've got a few ideas. I'll be running this whole place in no time.
Please. The Zhentarim can hold the Guildhall - but that's not the same as holding the Guild itself.
Leave.
I killed Raphael. In Hell. He's gone for good.
That's right, specialising in pre-owned goods. You want to trade, talk to Sticky there. I'm in management. Busy, you know?
You should know by now that I'm not everyone. If Raphael doesn't know that yet - he'll learn.
Well, look who it is. Looking to mess up my operation here, too? You'll find it a little harder than before.
So I'd suggest you just stick to business, yeah?
Are you going to destroy it?
Somehow, this is just the kind of place I'd expect to find you.
I found the contract you signed with Raphael, Mol. Do you want it?
Welcome on, welcome all. You're looking at Fetcher's Brats, the Guildhall's finest.
There's a fight for the city's survival coming. When it does, lend me the power of your pact.
Ready to do some business?

Synopsis:
Mol has signed a deal with Raphael.
She enjoys the power and wants to keep it to eventually run the Guildhall.
